Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.45,0:00:23.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他无意间发现了一个极大的威胁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he stumbled on a grave threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.72,0:00:31.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1966年 加州 帕萨迪纳 春季的某一天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Beautiful spring day, Pasadena, California. 1966.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.56,0:00:34.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们安居乐业\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Business is booming, life's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.99,0:00:38.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有一个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Except for one man,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.13,0:00:40.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}名叫克莱尔・彼得森的地质化学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a geochemist named Clair Patterson,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:42.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}朋友叫他帕特\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known as Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.30,0:00:49.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他认为他所看到的所有人都身处于无形的威胁中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He knows that everyone he sees is in danger from an invisible menace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.57,0:00:55.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他决心要阻止这一切\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he's determined to put a stop to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.57,0:00:57.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不计代价\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no matter what the cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:32.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第七集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.66,0:02:42.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了要说清楚彼得森的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can't really tell Pat Patterson's story
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.60,0:02:49.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}必须要从很久很久以前地球诞生前说起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without going all the way back to the time long before the earth our home, was built,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:52.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那时星星刚刚产生它的物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the stars brought forth its substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.47,0:02:55.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Iron
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:59.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带来了行星的炽热内核\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the planet's molten core.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:01.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.04,0:03:04.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带来了岩石 水和空气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the rocks and the water and the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.71,0:03:06.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:09.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带来了钻石和生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For diamonds. And life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:40.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一颗星诞生了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A star is born,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.39,0:03:43.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的星球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:47.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最初的几百万年里 一切还算顺利\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the first few million years, things ran smoothly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:51.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尘土颗粒滚雪球般的逐渐变成更大的物体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as dust grains snowballed into progressively larger objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:57.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到这个物体大到一定程度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But once these objects grew massive enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.77,0:03:59.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有了足够的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to have sufficient gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.71,0:04:11.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们开始相互吸引 从而轨道相交相撞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they began pulling each other into crossing orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:23.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是我们的世界最初的模样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is how our world looked when it was new.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:26.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球表面没有地方可以幸免于难\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No part of the earth's surface could survive intact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:28.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一直到现在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from that time to the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.39,0:04:36.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}既然地球的幼年记录都不复存在了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, with all its birth and early childhood records erased,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.06,0:04:41.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们怎么才能确定地球真正的年纪呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how could we ever hope to know with any certainty the true age of our world?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:45.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是个自古以来的谜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People have been wondering about this since antiquity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.36,0:04:51.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1650年 爱尔兰大主教詹姆斯・乌舍尔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1650 archbishop James Ussher of Ireland
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.76,0:04:55.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}得出一个貌似正确的结论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}made a calculation that seemed to settle the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:59.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就和当时大多数人一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like almost everyone else of his time and his world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:02.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的根据是圣经的造物论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he accepted the biblical account of creation as authoritative.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:05.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是圣经里也没有提到具体的年代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the Bible does not give exact years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}于是乌舍尔在旧约中寻找一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so Ussher searched for an event in the Old Testament
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.81,0:05:10.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与已知历史事件相吻合的时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that corresponded to a known historical date.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:13.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在列王记下卷中发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He found it in the second book of kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:19.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巴比伦统治者尼布甲尼撒二世死于公元前562年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the death of the Babylonian ruler Nebuchadnezzar in 562 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.31,0:05:23.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}乌舍尔将世代的先知和族长加起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Usher added up the generations of the prophets and the Patriarchs,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:27.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旧约中的139个族谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the 139 "Begats" of the Old Testament,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:30.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从亚当一直到尼布甲尼撒二世\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between Adam and the time of Nebuchadnezzar,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:31.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个世界诞生于10月22号\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the world began on October 22
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.76,0:05:36.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}公元前4004年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the year 4004 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:39.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}下午六点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At 6:00 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.16,0:05:41.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星期六\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.16,0:05:45.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}乌舍尔大主教制定的年表在当时的西方被奉为真理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Archbishop Ussher's chronology was taken as gospel in the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.83,0:05:49.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到我们通过另一种途径了解地球的年纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until we turned to another book to find the age of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:52.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过研究岩石本身的记录\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the one that was written in the rocks themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:55.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科罗拉多大峡谷中大多数的岩层\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the rock layers in the walls of the Grand Canyon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.27,0:05:58.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都属于沉积岩 由许多细小的颗粒堆积而成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are made of sediments, deposited as fine grains
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:02.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些沉积岩形成的时候 这里还是海洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a time when this part of the world was a sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:13.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}年复一年 沉积物被不断增加的新沉积物压缩成了岩石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over eons, the sediments were compressed into rock under the weight of succeeding layers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.28,0:06:15.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最下面的就是最古老的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the oldest ones at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.02,0:06:25.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随便选一层\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pick a layer, any layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:34.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个怎么样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How about that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.26,0:06:43.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很久以前 这里水并不深\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once upon a time, there must have been shallow water here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.87,0:06:46.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在前寒武纪时期\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in the Precambrian period,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:48.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约10亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about a billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:51.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那时只有一种生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there was only one kind of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:57.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些蓝绿色的细菌忙着收获阳光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These blue-green bacteria were busy harvesting sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:58.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从而产生氧气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and making oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.81,0:07:00.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对他们来说那只是废气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For them, it was just a waste product,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:03.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但对于后来的动物 包括我们来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but for the animals who evolved later, including us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:06.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是孕育生命的呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was the breath of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:12.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}另选一层\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Okay. Pick another layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:13.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个怎么样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How about that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.38,0:07:18.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这层被称为光明天使页岩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This layer is known as the bright angel shale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:22.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成于5.3亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It formed about 530 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:28.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些足迹属于2.6亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These tracks were left 260 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.06,0:07:30.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你想知道地球的年纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you want to know the age of the earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.49,0:07:33.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要了解形成每一层所需的时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just figure out how long it took to deposit each layer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.49,0:07:35.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不需要把族谱加起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then, instead of counting the "Begats,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.90,0:07:37.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把这些层次加起来就够了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}add up all the layers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.73,0:07:39.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很简单吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Easy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:43.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一个问题 我们是根据观察这个过程得出的结论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just one problem, We know from observing this process,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.17,0:07:44.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为它还在持续\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it still happens today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:46.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在海洋中 在湖泊中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in oceans and lakes around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.70,0:07:50.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沉积层的形成时间长度各不相同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That sediments can be laid down at widely different rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:52.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通常都是非常的缓慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It usually happens very slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约1000年才有1英尺\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}say a foot of sediment per 1,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.84,0:07:57.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但如果发生了罕见的大洪灾\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when the's a rare catastrophic flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.84,0:07:59.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}速度就会快很多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it can happen much faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:02.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几天就已经有1英尺了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as much as a foot in just a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.35,0:08:17.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}许多地质学家尝试用这种方式来计算地球的年纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many geologists tried this method to calculate the age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.09,0:08:18.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们勘探了大峡谷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They used the Grand Canyon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.69,0:08:21.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有地球上其它的沉积层区域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other sedimentary sequences around the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.09,0:08:24.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是他们的结论差异却无法统一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But their answers ranged too widely to be of much use,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.09,0:08:27.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}差异范围从300万年到150亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anywhere between three million years and 15 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:34.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个方法还有其它的问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there were other problems with this method:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.00,0:08:36.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使最下层的岩石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the deepest layers of rock
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:39.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也不是地球上最古老的东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are not the oldest things on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.17,0:08:43.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为即使岩石也不能从地球最初所受的灾难中幸存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why? Because not even rocks could survive the earth's violent infancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:48.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而太空 那又是另一回事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In space it's another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:08.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球诞生时留下了任何的纪念品吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are there any mementos from when the earth was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:12.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有可以证明真实年龄的物体吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}objects that could possibly tell us its true age?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.12,0:09:16.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我知道一个地方 可以找到当年太阳系形成时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I know a place where the unused bricks and mortar left over
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:19.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}残留的遗迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the creation of our solar system can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:23.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们存在于木星和火星的轨道间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It lies between the orbits of Jupiter and Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:26.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些是产生地球的原料\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here is the stuff of the newborn earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:29.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们在冰冷的太空中飘荡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}adrift in cold storage, unchanged
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.23,0:09:31.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从未改变过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ever since that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.03,0:09:33.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}100万年左右之前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A million or so years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.03,0:09:38.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一颗大的小行星恰巧击撞了一颗较小的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a large asteroid happened to jostle a much smaller one,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.76,0:09:41.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将它推到一个新的轨道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sending it on a new trajectory,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:46.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的运动轨迹在大约5万年前的一个夜晚终结\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a collision course that ended one night some 50,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:14.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它从天空划过打破了大峡谷的平静\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It must have shattered the peace of the Grand Canyon as it sailed overhead...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.65,0:10:23.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}撞击形成这个大坑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to blast out this crater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.26,0:10:27.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即大峡谷所在的州
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.26,0:10:27.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在后来这里被称为 亚利桑那\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in what would one day be known as Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:40.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这颗铁质小行星的碎片\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fragments of the iron asteroid that made this crater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.67,0:10:43.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被完整的保留了下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have survived intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.40,0:10:46.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们知道这块铁的形成时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we just knew how long ago that iron was forged,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:47.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们就能知道太阳系的年龄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'd know the age of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.01,0:10:49.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也包括地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Including the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.47,0:10:51.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怎么才能知道呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how could we know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.34,0:10:52.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}挑块石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pick a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:55.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随便一块石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Any rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:10:59.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个怎么样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How about that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:03.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这块石头中的某些原子可能具有放射性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some atoms in this rock could be radioactive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:06.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们自然地发生衰变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which means they spontaneously disintegrate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.15,0:11:07.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从而变成其它元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and become other elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.85,0:11:11.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铀原子首先变成钍原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A uranium atom first becomes a thorium atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.62,0:11:14.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}平均而言 耗时十几亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On average, it takes a few billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:17.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}钍很不稳定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thorium is much more unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.12,0:11:19.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不到一个月的时间就能变成镤\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In less than a month it turns into protactinium.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:24.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一分钟后 镤又变成了其它元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A minute later, protactinium becomes something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.33,0:11:28.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又经过10次的核转变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The atom undergoes ten more nuclear transmutations...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:31.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来到衰变链的最后一环\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until it reaches the last stop on the decay chain:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:31.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}衰变链指的是放射性衰变过程中成链产生的一系列衰变产物
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:35.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个稳定的铅原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A stable atom of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.47,0:11:40.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铅将不再发生变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And lead it will remain... For eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.30,0:11:46.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}20世纪有个巨大的成就  在几十年里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 20th century there was a huge effort, lasting decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.67,0:11:51.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}测量每种放射性元素转变成另一种元素所用的时间后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to measure the time it takes for each radioactive element to transmute into another element.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:55.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物理学家发现每个不稳定元素的原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Physicists discovered that the atoms of each unstable element
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.51,0:11:57.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}衰变比率是恒定的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}decay at a constant rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:12:01.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子的原子核就像一座圣殿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nucleus of an atom is a kind of sanctuary,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:06.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无视震动和环境的改变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}immune to the shocks and upheavals of its environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.22,0:12:08.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用锤子砸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hit it with a hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.19,0:12:15.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在油里炸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Boil it in oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.23,0:12:23.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}气化它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vaporize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:26.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子钟走的不紧不慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nuclear clock goes on ticking,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.23,0:12:28.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一跳的时间都绝对标准\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}keeping an absolute standard of time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:31.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不论日月星辰的变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that does not look to the sun and the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.57,0:12:36.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要了解地球真实的年龄 没有比测量铀原子更好的办法了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What better way to find the true age of the earth than with the uranium atom?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.87,0:12:40.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要知道岩石中铀衰变成铅的比率\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you knew what fraction of the uranium in a rock had turned into lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:45.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就可以计算出岩石存在了多久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you could calculate how much time had passed since the rock was formed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.21,0:12:47.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但有个问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:49.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成之初的那些岩石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rocks in the earth that were present when it was formed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.48,0:12:51.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都已不复存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.58,0:12:57.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或被压碎了 或被融化了 或者被重塑了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've all been crushed, melted, remade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.72,0:13:01.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有个办法可以计算出铅的最初数量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a way to calculate the amount of lead that was present from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.32,0:13:02.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天赐的礼物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a gift from the heavens:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:04.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}陨石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Meteorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:10.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这块碎片来自造成这个大坑的陨石 很理想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This one... A fragment of the one that made this giant crater... Was ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:13.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这块陨石中铅的含量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The amount of lead deep inside this meteorite
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.09,0:13:15.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与地球形成时的完全一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is exactly the same as when earth formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.93,0:13:19.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}既然知道了铀衰变的固定比率\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since you know the constant rate of uranium decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.36,0:13:21.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就可以知道这块陨石的年龄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that should give you the age of the meteorite,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:25.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和地球的年龄一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which was made at the same time as the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.06,0:13:26.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要测量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All you had to do was measure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:29.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}陨石中的铅就行了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the amount of lead in meteorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:32.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很简单吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Easy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.91,0:13:41.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位在芝加哥大学名叫哈理森・布朗的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A scientist named Harrison Brown at the University of Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:45.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1947年首次掌握了这个方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first understood this in 1947.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:49.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他选择了一位研究生来实际操作 克莱尔・彼得森\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He chose a young graduate student, Clair Patterson, to do the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:55.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时彼得森怎么也不会想到这个作业\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Patterson couldn't possibly know how this assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.28,0:13:57.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会改变他的一生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would alter the course of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有这个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.09,0:14:16.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}表面上只是单纯的科学研究\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What seemed like pure scientific research
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.66,0:14:18.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}结果却不简单\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}turned out to be so much more.
