Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.65,0:20:57.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}小伙伴们很亲密呦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's an electron between friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:03.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}杜绝了样本被外界的铅污染后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Having isolated the sample from any outside lead contamination,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.19,0:21:09.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}彼得森终于可以测量样本中的铅和铀的含量了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Patterson was, at last, ready to measure the amount of lead and uranium in the sample
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.33,0:21:13.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且测定它形成的年代了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and calculate how many years before it had formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:15.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的真实年龄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The true age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.97,0:21:21.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感谢所有做出过贡献的科学家们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thank you to all the scientists who came before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:25.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感谢地质学家们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thank you, geologists.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.20,0:21:27.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感谢查尔斯・莱尔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thank you, Charles Lyell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.20,0:21:27.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}著名地质学家 均变说的重要论述者
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.97,0:21:33.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感谢迈克尔・法拉第\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thank you, Michael Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.97,0:21:33.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}发现电磁感应
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.14,0:21:42.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约瑟夫・汤姆森\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}J.J. Thomson.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.14,0:21:42.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}发现电子
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:50.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欧内斯特・卢瑟福\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ernest Rutherford.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:50.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}核物理之父
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:22:01.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感谢哈里森・布朗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thank you, Harrison Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:22:01.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}研究如何分开钸和铀
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.53,0:22:13.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的年龄是45亿岁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The world is four and a half billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:16.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们成功了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:29.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}妈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.31,0:22:31.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}妈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.11,0:22:33.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}彼得森想最先把这个困扰他多年的谜团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Patterson wanted his mother to be the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.43,0:22:37.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与他的母亲分享\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to know what he had struggled for so many years to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:40.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的真实年龄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The true age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.58,0:22:45.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这项发现为他带来什么奖励吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His reward for this discovery?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.55,0:22:47.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天大的麻烦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A world of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.65,0:22:51.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他当时并不知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He didn't know it, but he was on a collision course
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.03,0:22:55.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他妨碍了某些世界上最有权力的人的利益\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with some of the most powerful people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.52,0:23:24.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对于古罗马人来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To the ancient Romans,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:27.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}雄伟的土星并不是一个地点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the majestic ringed planet Saturn was not a real place,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:27.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其单词也有农神的意思
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.92,0:23:30.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也不是星球 而是天神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not a world, but a God King,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:33.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天地结合的结晶\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a son of the marriage of heaven and earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.76,0:23:38.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铅神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the God of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.06,0:23:43.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些立柱都是罗马广场上最古老神庙的遗迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These columns are all that remain of this oldest temple in the Roman forum
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.87,0:23:47.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最早是在2500年前供奉农神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first consecrated to Saturn 2,500 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.43,0:23:50.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}后来用做罗马的金库\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It also served as Rome's treasury
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.10,0:23:52.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也做过计量局\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its bureau of weights and measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.00,0:23:58.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}今天是古罗马的农神节\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tonight is Saturnalia,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.04,0:24:00.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向农神表示敬意的12月狂欢节\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the wild december holiday in Saturn's honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.44,0:24:02.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日常生活行为彻底颠倒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And everyday life will be turned upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.88,0:24:05.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}主人为奴仆服务\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The masters will serve the slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.21,0:24:07.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}停止一切战争和死刑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no wars or executions will be allowed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.68,0:24:09.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们相互给予礼物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gifts will be exchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.58,0:24:11.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几百年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A couple of hundred years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.28,0:24:15.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当早年间的牧师们想要吸引更多教徒时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the early church fathers look for a way to attract more pagans,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:18.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们把农神节变成了圣诞节\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they'll decide to turn Saturnalia into Christmas,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.25,0:24:22.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给这个冬季的节日赋予了新的意义\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making it the latest in a long line of winter solstice holidays to be re-purposed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.39,0:24:37.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在农神节的夜晚这个高耸的农神神像看上去好像是这个样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This towering statue of Saturn may have look something like this on the night of saturnalia
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.93,0:24:42.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是在古罗马 他还有更阴暗的一面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in ancient Rome, this God had another, darker side.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.80,0:24:47.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}农神是一个冷酷的愤懑的行动迟缓的食尸鬼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That other Saturn is a cold and sullen, sluggish ghoul,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.90,0:24:50.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}动不动就乱发脾气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}given to irrational bouts of rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.97,0:24:55.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她对他父亲的罪行难以言喻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He committed an unspeakable act of violence against his father,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.07,0:24:57.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至吞噬了自己的孩子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and devoured his own children.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.61,0:25:01.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在所有古人能用肉眼看见的行星中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all the planets visible to the unaided eyes of the ancients
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.81,0:25:04.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}土星的速度是最慢的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is the slowest,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.28,0:25:08.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这也就是古人用铅神的名字为他命名的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which could explain why it's named after the God of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.12,0:25:12.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不可否认的是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's no denying
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.82,0:25:14.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}农神性格的阴暗面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the more negative aspects of Saturn's personality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.92,0:25:18.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实反映的是古代人们对于铅中毒的认识\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reflect the age-old knowledge of the symptoms of lead poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.92,0:25:20.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有意思的是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Funny thing about the Romans.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.42,0:25:22.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管他们知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though they knew
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.06,0:25:24.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}接触铅会使人中毒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that contact with lead inevitably poisoned people,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.56,0:25:26.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}造成不育还有发狂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rendered them sterile and drove them mad,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.96,0:25:29.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你猜他们是用的什么材料\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what metal did they use to make the pipes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.13,0:25:31.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}修建他们大名鼎鼎的供水管道呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that carried the water through their legendary aqueducts?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.70,0:25:33.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给你个提示\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'll give you a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.70,0:25:35.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}水管这个词\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The word "plumbing" comes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.50,0:25:39.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是来源于拉丁文里的 铅\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Latin word for lead, "plumbum."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.31,0:25:53.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们用什么金属制造他们的浴缸呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What metal did they use to line their famous baths?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.91,0:25:57.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果葡萄酒太酸时他们怎么办呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And how did they sweeten their wines when they were too sour?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:26:01.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的锅碗瓢盆又是什么材料呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What did they use to line their vats and cooking pots?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.45,0:26:03.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}部分历史学家相信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are some historians who believe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.58,0:26:06.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铅的广泛使用是造成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the widespread use of lead was a major cause
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.95,0:26:09.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}罗马帝国覆灭的主因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the decline and fall of the Roman Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.75,0:26:14.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么他们在知道铅有毒后还继续使用呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why did they continue to use lead long after they knew it was toxic?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:20.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为它便宜 延展性好 制造简单\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was cheap, very malleable, easy to work with,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.42,0:26:23.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大量接触致命剂量的那些人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the ones who were exposed to it at its most lethal levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.49,0:26:25.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}矿工和处理铅的工人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the miners and workers who processed the lead...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.90,0:26:27.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是无关紧要的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were considered expendable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.93,0:26:29.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的性命不重要\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their lives didn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.93,0:26:31.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们是奴隶\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.80,0:26:37.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上大部分的铅最初都是深埋在地下 与生物保持安全的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the earth's lead started off at a safe distance from living things, down below the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.40,0:26:39.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是大约8500年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but about 8,500 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.77,0:26:42.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们知道了如何从地里挖东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}humans began figuring out how to dig into the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.91,0:26:44.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从岩石中提炼金属\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and extract metals from rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.51,0:26:46.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个庄园新建成时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By the time this villa was new,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.67,0:26:48.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就几千年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just a couple of thousand years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.97,0:26:53.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}罗马人年产铅8万吨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the romans were producing 80,000 tons of lead a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.41,0:26:58.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么铅对我们的危害这么大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is lead so poisonous to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.25,0:27:00.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为当铅进入我们的体内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because when it gets into our bodies,
